ers": {"type": "object", "properties": {"plan": {"description": "Markdown text describing the step-by-step plan (bullet list).", "title": "Plan", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["plan"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "check_progress", "description": "Log a progress note and return a JSON snapshot of deliverables + plan excerpt.\n\nAppends `<UTC ISO timestamp> <note>` to `workspace/.progress.log`, then\nreturns a JSON string containing:\n  - `output_files`: list of {name, size_bytes} under `workspace/output/`.\n  - `success_artifact_present`: whether the task's success artifact glob matches.\n  - `plan_excerpt`: first 1000 chars of `.plan.md` (or empty if missing).\n  - `note_count`: total notes logged so far.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"note": {"description": "Short progress note to append to the log (plain text, one line).", "title": "Note", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["note"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "submit_done", "description": "End the episode. Set success=true only if criteria met (agent-declared).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"success": {"description": "Whether the agent believes the task objective is satisfied.", "title": "Success", "type": "boolean"}, "summary": {"default": "", "description": "Short optional note for logging.", "title": "Summary", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["success"]}}}], "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "# Task `riya_limma`\n\n# Real R-task: riya_limma\n\n**Pipeline provenance:** `RiyaDua-cervical-cancer-snakemake-workflow` (family: `rna`).\nThis workspace is derived from a real R script in the source workflow. The ground-truth\nreference output used for offline scoring lives outside this workspace and is not\naccessible to you during execution.\n\n## Your goal\n\nYou are given:\n  - `input/expression.csv`: expression matrix (genes x samples; first column = gene id).\n  - `input/metadata.csv`: sample metadata with a `group` column (`normal` vs `cancer`).\n\nUsing the limma pipeline (lmFit + contrasts `cancer - normal` + eBayes), compute the top\n250 differentially expressed genes and write them (csv) to `output/deg_results.csv`.\nUse `write.csv(deg_results, 'output/deg_results.csv')` so the first column is the gene id.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/deg_results.csv` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: deg_results.csv, volcano.png under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"expression.csv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"expression.csv\"\n    },\n    \"metadata.csv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"metadata.csv\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/deg_results.csv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_45NMApKtnBESMYZzTVXybXBr", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{}", "name": "list_workdir"}}, {"id": "call_euJUOpWOl0LgVeMp72IWhnsO", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"expression.csv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"expression.csv\"\n    },\n    \"metadata.csv\": {\n      \"_file\": \"metadata.csv\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}", "name": "list_workdir", "tool_call_id": "call_45NMApKtnBESMYZzTVXybXBr"}, {"role": "tool", "content": "# Real R-task: riya_limma\n\n**Pipeline provenance:** `RiyaDua-cervical-cancer-snakemake-workflow` (family: `rna`).\nThis workspace is derived from a real R script in the source workflow. The ground-truth\nreference output used for offline scoring lives outside this workspace and is not\naccessible to you during execution.\n\n## Your goal\n\nYou are given:\n  - `input/expression.csv`: expression matrix (genes x samples; first column = gene id).\n  - `input/metadata.csv`: sample metadata with a `group` column (`normal` vs `cancer`).\n\nUsing the limma pipeline (lmFit + contrasts `cancer - normal` + eBayes), compute the top\n250 differentially expressed genes and write them (csv) to `output/deg_results.csv`.\nUse `write.csv(deg_results, 'output/deg_results.csv')` so the first column is the gene id.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/deg_results.csv` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: deg_results.csv, volcano.png under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n", "name": "read_text_file", "tool_call_id": "call_euJUOpWOl0LgVeMp72IWhnsO"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_qyZnUi99ROwCzh5YLdEZVhZl", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Read `input/expression.csv` and `input/metadata.csv`.\\n2. Use the limma package to perform differential expression analysis:\\n   - Fit linear model using `lmFit`.\\n   - Define contrasts `cancer - normal`.\\n   - Apply `eBayes` to compute statistics.\\n3. Extract top 250 differentially expressed genes.\\n4. Write results to `output/deg_results.csv` with gene ids as the first column.\\n5. Generate a volcano plot and save it as `output/volcano.png`.\\n6. Validate the existence of `output/deg_results.csv` and `output/volcano.png`.\\n7. Submit the task as done if outputs are correct.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (573 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_qyZnUi99ROwCzh5YLdEZVhZl"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls"